<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Beats Sichuan in China Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Wanda beat Sichuan Quanxin
3-1 in Chengdu, central Sichuan, on Sunday to extend its unbeaten
streak to 38 games after the fourth round of China's first
division professional soccer league.
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless first half, Wang Tao opened the scoring for
Dalian in the 53rd minute, only to see Quanxin tied it 1-1 one
minute later through a header from Liu Bin.
</P>
<P>
Dalian surged ahead again in the 77th minute as Wang converted
a Hao Haidong pass and completed the mauling in the last minute
with a goal from Li Ming.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches, 10-man Guangzhou Apollo rallied from
behind to overcome Vanguard Huandao 2-1, Tianjin Samsung beat
Qingdao Hainiu 1-0, while Jilin Aodong forced a scoreless tie with
Guangdong Hongyuan.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guoan tied with August First and Jinan Taishan drew
with Shanghai Shenhua, both with 1-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
