<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Hails Sino-French Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao Shi said that from an overall point of view, the
construction of China's modernization and its building-up of
democratic politics conform to each other.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully aware that it is an arduous task to develop
democracy in China, as our country has a vast area and a huge
population, and its level of economic and cultural development is
not high yet. Moreover, it had a feudalistic history of thousands
of years," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China, while developing its economy, will
unswervingly push forward the building-up of democracy and a legal
system steadily and from the country's actual conditions.
</P>
<P>
"Through our efforts, a socialist, democratic political system
with Chinese characteristics will definitely be established in
China," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that the 8th NPC will waste no time in the remaining
part of 1997 to shape the framework of a set of laws for
protecting and serving the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the NPC will continue to work on the laws
aimed at pushing forward the building-up of socialist and
democratic political system, including the drafting of a
surveillance code to institutionalize and make into law the
supervision by the legislative bodies at all levels over the
country's administrations, courts, public prosecution bodies and
other state organs.
</P>
<P>
He said that those measures will have an important influence on
the building-up of a democratic political system in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
