<HEADLINE> Workshop on Women's Skill Development Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A national workshop opened here
today to train those working in the field of women's skill
development from throughout Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, jointly organized by the International Labor
Organization (ILO) and a local institute, is aimed at providing
training to workers of the social organizations being engaged in
the promotion of women entrepreneurship in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Industry Minister Keshav Prasad Badal told the workshop
that the government will work out laws and policies aimed at
empowering women especially from backward communities.
</P>
<P>
He also called for more vocational training courses for women
to enable them to run enterprises on their own.
</P>
<P>
An ILO official told the workshop that the ILO is actively
involved in small industry development in Nepal as small-scale
enterprises could absorb a large number of unemployed people and
contribute to poverty alleviation.
</P>
<P>
A total of 34 women representatives from various
non-governmental and governmental agencies in Nepal are taking
part in the workshop.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
