<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in 2 Schools in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A Yemeni today opened machine gun
fire at two high schools here, killing seven people, including
three children, and wounding some others, according to security
sources.
</P>
<P>
The gunman, identified as Hassan Ali al-Baadani, was injured
in an exchange of fire with security forces. He is now in police
custody.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that he waited in front of the gate of
Al-Tallai private high school, where his two daughters attend.
</P>
<P>
He fatally shot the headmistress of the school and killed a
cafeteria employee who rushed to cover her body and wounded a bus
driver who tried to block him from entering the school.
</P>
<P>
The gunman shot dead three children and one teacher inside the
school before going to a nearby School to kill another teacher.
</P>
</TEXT>
