<HEADLINE> President Seeking Views of Constitutional Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Indian President S.D. Sharma
was seeking views from constitutional and legal experts tonight on
steps to be taken following Congress's move to withdraw its
support for the United Front government, the Press Trust of India
(PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The Congress Party has staked a claimed to form the next
government while some leaders of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP),
the biggest opposition in the country, have also expressed their
willingness to form the government.
</P>
<P>
The United Front government tonight ruled out resignation
following withdrawal of support by the Congress, and demanded an
opportunity to prove its majority in the Lower House of
parliament, according to Jaipal Reddy, spokesman for the United
Front government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
