<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New UAE Cabinet Sworn In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A 23-member new cabinet of the
United Arab Emirates (UAE) was sworn in today by President Sheikh
Zayed Bin Sultan Al Nahyan.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet, formed last Tuesday, is under the premiership of
Sheikh Maktoum Bin Rashid, UAE Vice President and the ruler of
Dubai, the second biggest of the seven sheikdoms of the UAE. It is
the sixth cabinet since the founding of the UAE in December 2,
1971.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet has 21 ministers of whom eight are new
faces. Maktoum tendered the resignation of his former cabinet on
March 16 and was charged the same day by Al Nahyan to form the new
one.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle had been expected as some ministers held more than
two portfolios and some others were ill.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, Al Nahyan hoped that each cabinet member
would shoulder the full responsibility in his field, indicating
the importance of national action in the coming phase and
asserting the need to work for the good and welfare of the UAE
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
