<HEADLINE> Typhoid Cases Rise in Ethiopia's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The number of typhoid cases
in Addis Ababa, the capital of Ethiopia, rose to 3,282 in the
first half of the Ethiopian year which started on September 11,
1996 and will end on September 10, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The figure registered stood at 2,929 last year, the Addis
Ababa regional health bureau said today.
</P>
<P>
Ayele Belachew, the head of the Epidemic Diseases Prevention
and Control Unit in the bureau, said the main cause of the
increase is lack of sanitation.
</P>
<P>
He advised the public to refrain from consuming contaminated
food and drink.
</P>
<P>
Strong preventive and control campaigns are being carried out
against the disease, he said, adding that both the professionals
and the public are now relieved much from the threat posed by
typhoid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
