<HEADLINE> Salim: Africans Should Travel in Africa with Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Organization of African Unity
(OAU) Secretary-General Salim Ahamed Salim has called for the
removal of visa restrictions among African nations as a means to
boost intra-African trade.
</P>
<P>
"If West African countries in ECOWAS (Economic Community of
West African States) could do this successfully all these years,
I do not see the reason why other sub-regional blocs in the
continent cannot do the same," Salim was quoted by the News
Agency of Nigeria today.
</P>
<P>
African states should eliminate administrative and other
barriers to free movement of people and goods on the continent,
Salim said at the opening ceremony of the seventh OAU/AEC
All-Africa Trade and Tourism Fair in Kaduna, northern Nigeria, on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He urged African countries to rationalize their policies to
encourage the development of the private sector, which he said
was in a better shape to direct the economic development efforts
of African economies in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
According to Salim, a research project sponsored by the OAU on
sourcing of pharmaceutical requirements of eastern and southern
African countries has found that 60 percent of their needs could
be sourced locally.
</P>
<P>
He enjoined the African business community to seize the
opportunity of the fair to evolve ways of promoting
intra-continent trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
