<HEADLINE> INTERPOL to Train West African Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The International Police
Organization (INTERPOL) has worked out plans to train policemen
in the West African sub-region to reflect its operation capacity.
</P>
<P>
The related countries wil have opportunities to learn the
latest information technology acquired by INTERPOL, said Ismaila
Seck, the coordinator of INTERPOL's regional bureau for Africa,
</P>
<P>
