<HEADLINE> Jordan Calls for "Liberating Palestinian Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, March 30 (Xinhua) - Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan today
called for closer Jordanian-Palestinian economic ties so as to
"liberate Palestinian economy from Israeli domination", Radio
Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
While meeting the press at Jordan Television, Hassan said that
70 percent of Palestinian economy was dependent on Israel. The
situation should be changed through opening to Jordan the Arab
land belonging to the Palestinians, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hassan said this could serve the interests of both Jordanians
and Palestinians and contribute to liberating the Palestinians
from Israeli political and economic "domination."
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian question was the central issue to Jordan and
this embodied the kingdom's policies toward peace in the region,
he underlined.
</P>
<P>
A sovereign state for the Palestinians should be established
and various Palestinian rights, including that of
self-determination on their own land, be realized as part of the
comprehensive settlement to the Arab-Israeli dispute, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jordan rejected the Israeli government's Jewish settlement
policy in Arab East Jerusalem and considered it a breach of
international law and obstacle to peace.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein of Jordan, accompanied by Prime Minister
Abdul-Salam Majali, is currently in the United States and will
meet with U.S. President Bill Clinton and other U.S. officials to
seek solutions to the stalemated Arab-Israeli dispute. 
</P>
