<HEADLINE> Exposition on China Held in Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liege (Belgium), March 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese paintings, works
of calligraphy and some cultural relics went on display at an
exposition held in Belgium today.
</P>
<P>
The exposition was organized by the Belgium-China Association
and its collaborators in Liege, a city in eastern Belgium.
</P>
<P>
A collection of Chinese traditional paintings and works of
calligraphy won praise from many Belgian visitors. Chinese artists
gave on-the-spot demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
A briefing on tourism sites in China was also given at the
exposition. Some visitors said that they were eager to see what
China was really like at a time when the sovereignty of Hong Kong
would be handed over to China on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Franck Willems, president of the Belgium-China Association, and
Edmond Leburton, former Belgian prime minister, attended the
exposition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
