<HEADLINE> Uganda to Host African Home Economic Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Uganda will host the third All
African Home Economic Conference's general assembly in Kampala
from April 4 to 11, according to its organizers here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference will bring together home economists from
Africa, America, Europe, Asia.
</P>
<P>
The theme for this year's conference is "Home Economics for
Empowerment and Development, Implications for
Reconceptualization".
</P>
<P>
The conference is being organized by the Home Economics
Association for Africa and the Uganda Home Economics Association.
</P>
<P>
The World Home Economics Day is an annual event observed on
March 21 every year all over the world.
</P>
<P>
However, in Uganda, the day was observed Friday with a charity
walk in and around Kampala led by Minister of State for Gender
and Community Development Janet Francis Muka.
</P>
<P>
The charity walk was part of the preparatory activities in
which the home economists seek to raise awareness among the
public about the role of home economics as well as to raise funds
for the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
