<HEADLINE> UAE President: No Peace, Security Without </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- United Arab Emirates (UAE)
President Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan Al-Nahyan today asserted that
there would be no peace and security without the restoration of
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks while addressing the new
cabinet members who were sworn in today. He said that the
challenges facing the peace process require a decisive Arab
stand.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the UAE stood by the side of the Palestinian
people until they restored their full rights to their homeland
and territories.
</P>
<P>
Israel ought to reconsider its position and give up its
settlement policy, and commit itself to the accords concluded
with the Palestinians, he said.
</P>
<P>
The UAE new cabinet, formed last Tuesday, has 21 ministers. It
is the 6th cabinet since the founding of the UAE in December 2,
1971.
</P>
<P>
The president called upon each cabinet member to shoulder his
full responsibility, indicating the importance of national action
in the coming phase and asserting the need to work for the good
and welfare of the UAE people. 
</P>
