<HEADLINE> Zhenhai Refining Builds China's Largest Oil Dock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Zhenhai Refining, a company listed
on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, has built a 250,000-ton oil dock,
the country's largest, in a bid to reduce its transportation costs.
</P>
<P>
The dock was upgraded from its original 150,000 tons, and
received formal acknowledgement from the competent government
department today.
</P>
<P>
The project was completed at the end of 1994 after eight months
of construction.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jiaren, general manager of Zhenhai Refining, said that
the state-owned company, whose crude oil mainly comes from the
international market, plans to push its annual oil refining
capacity to 16 million tons by the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
He said that the boosting of the dock's capacity will reduce
the company's transportation costs by about 20 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
