<HEADLINE> Qiao Calls for Closer Ties Between NPC, European Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of China, on
Sunday hailed the relations between the NPC and the European
Parliament.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Paris-based Chinese language newspaper
"Nouvelles d'Europe", Qiao said that the two sides have increased
contacts since China and the European Union (EU) established
official relations in 1975.
</P>
<P>
Qiao hoped that his visit to France and Italy, the first time a
Chinese NPC leader has visited EU members, would deepen the
understanding and promote cooperation between the NPC and the
European Parliament.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and the EU are two important forces on the
world political stage, and that China values the role of the
European Parliament as one of the major EU institutions.
</P>
<P>
He said that the NPC hopes to increase exchanges with the
European Parliament as a way of boosting the overall Sino-European
relationship.
</P>
<P>
On the differences between the two sides over certain issues,
Qiao said that China prefers to have dialogue with the European
Parliament in order to deepen mutual understanding, narrow
differences and enhance cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said he is confident that the relations between China and
the EU and those between the NPC and the European Parliament will
develop on a steady and healthy basis as long as the two sides
stick to the principles of mutual respect, seeking common ground
while reserving differences, non-interference in each other's
internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
