<HEADLINE> Senior Official Calls For Further Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Efforts must be made to further
ensure agricultural development, higher income for farmers and
stability in rural areas, by closely following the Party's
agriculture-related policies, said a senior official of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, an alternate member of the Political Bureau and
member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, stressed
the point during a recent five-day visit to Shouyang County in
north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The situation in rural areas is getting better, but more
priority should be given to agriculture to get good harvests, he
said, adding that officials at all levels must put agriculture at
the top of the agenda in developing the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The Party has adopted a series of policies to consolidate the
work in agriculture, he said. And effective measures must be taken
to solve serious problems that arise in rural reform and
development, such as the problem in purchasing, marketing and
storage of farm products, he added.
</P>
<P>
Steps also must be taken to lighten the burden on peasants and
make the most of their initiative, he said.
</P>
<P>
Rural infrastructure construction must be quickened to improve
production conditions, and efforts should be made to increase the
contributions of science and technology in promoting rural
economic growth, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He called on major grain producers like Shouyang to develop a
diversified economy while holding onto grain production. Work must
be done to increase the added value of farm products, and to boost
agricultural modernization, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
