<HEADLINE> Writers Discuss Promoting China's Environment Literature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Some 60 well-known Chinese
writers gathered here today to discuss the development of China's
literature on the environment, and to celebrate the publication of
the country's first collected works in the field.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siyuan, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress; Zhang Qie, vice-chairman of the
Chinese Writers' Association; and Zhang Kunmin, deputy-director of
the State Bureau of Environmental Protection, attended the forum.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kunmin said that environmental protection is one of the
state's basic policies. Since China determined the policy of
sustainable development last year, the public's awareness of
environmental protection has greatly improved, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang added that the environment-oriented literature, with its
vivid style, lauds outstanding people and good deeds while
criticizing uncivilized behavior. The literature has an
"irreplaceable role" in upgrading the public's awareness of
environmental protection, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Many writers spoke at the forum, saying that it is urgent to
give full play to the role of literature in improving the public's
awareness of environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they expressed the hope that more writers will
devote themselves to the field, pushing forward the development of
China's writings on environment.
</P>
<P>
The new collection includes the works of 140 writers. Xie
Zhenhua, director of the State Bureau of Environmental Protection,
wrote the preface for the book. 
</P>
</TEXT>
