<HEADLINE> China to Improve Natural Disaster Reduction Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The China Committee of the
International Decade for Disaster Reduction has approved in
principle draft of the "People's Republic of China Disaster
Reduction Outline" at its ongoing seventh plenary meeting.
</P>
<P>
Li Guixian, state councillor and head of the committee, said
that the outline defines China's development strategy and
objectives in reducing natural disasters. It also will serve to
promote China's disaster reduction drive, inform the international
community of China's long-term plans, and seek international
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He called on localities to increase the awareness of disaster
reduction and concentrate on development of the work. Efforts
should be made to effectively reduce the effects of natural
disasters and ensure sustainable social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
The outline, which was initiated in 1994, describes China's
current situation in disaster reduction, its strategy and
policies, and ways and fields that enjoy first priority for
international cooperation.  
