<HEADLINE> Bank Grants Loans to Shanghai Subway Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Communications, one
of the major Chinese commercial banks headquartered in Shanghai,
today issued another 600 million yuan in loans for the second line
of the city's subway project.
</P>
<P>
Bank officials say that the bank will continue its financial
aid until the completion of the project, which will help upgrade
the investment environment of Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the subway project will need a total of 10.5
billion yuan in investment, the sources say.
</P>
<P>
Pudong New Area is an emerging financial and trade hub of the
city, separated from the downtown area of Shanghai by the Huangpu
River.
</P>
<P>
The second line project of the Shanghai subway will connect
Pudong New Area with the city's downtown areas on the opposite
side of the river through an underground channel.
</P>
<P>
The sources say that the bank has issued a total of 900 million
yuan of loans to two key urban public transportation projects,
including the subway project, since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The bank has been actively involved in the construction of
local infrastructural projects over the past decade, and invested
heavily in them.  
</P>
