<HEADLINE> Iraq to Start Food Distribution to Citizens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 3l (Xinhua) -- Iraq has decided to start food
distribution as of next month in accordance with the
implementation of an oil-for-food deal with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency (INA) today quoted an unnamed Iraqi
Trade Ministry spokesman as announcing that each citizen will
get nine kilograms of flour.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that other food supplies set for each
citizen will start to be distributed from May.
</P>
<P>
The present quota of flour for each citizen in the country is
seven kilograms a month, which is insufficient, so Iraqis are
compelled to buy additional amounts of flour at high prices.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese ship loaded with Thailand rice reached the Umm Qasr
Port in southern Iraq on March 26, the first shipment of food
supplies to arrive in Iraq by sea since the oil-for-food deal
between Iraq and the U.N. was finalized.
</P>
<P>
Iraq was allowed last December to sell 2 billion U.S. dollars
worth of oil to buy food and other necessities over a six-month
period to alleviate the sufferings of its people due to more than
six years of U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The INA today quoted an official source at the Iraqi Trade
Ministry as saying that 14 other ships carrying food supplies
will get to Iraq in the coming days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
