<HEADLINE> Albania Asks Italy to Solve Refugee Boat Issue Properly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian government said today
the sinking of an Albanian refugee boat was not caused by Italy's
policy but the tragedy could be avoided.
</P>
<P>
An Albanian government spokesman said that Albania is satisfied
with the ongoing investigation into the incident by the Italian
judicial bodies.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the outcome of the investigation would help
further improve the friendly ties between the two countries
instead of destroying them.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government asked Italy to try to find all bodies
of the drowned refugees and reconsider its attitude toward
Albanian refugees already there.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks, nearly 13,000 Albanian refugees have
thronged into Italy.
</P>
<P>
On March 28, a refugee boat which left the southern Albanian
port of Vlore for Italy with 117 Albanians on board, sank in the
Adriatic Sea after colliding with an Italian warship named Sibilla.
</P>
<P>
So far, only 34 survivors have been found and 79 people on
board confirmed to be dead.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government declared March 31 a "national day of
mourning" for the victims of the tragedy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
