<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Urges Young Scientists For Bold Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
urged the country's young scientists to open their minds and be
adventurous in their research in order to make greater
contributions to the development of science and technology and
the socialist modernization of the country.
</P>
<P>
Li made the request during a meeting with a group of Chinese
scientists, all under 45, from the Chinese Academy of
Sciences. The group gathered in Beijing to discuss the necessity
of nurturing young scientists and to study ways to perfect
policies in this respect.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed his pleasure at discovering that the
scientists, all pioneers in their fields, are so young.
</P>
<P>
