Zedong once said to us, 'Young people are like the sun at eight or
nine in the morning, our hope rests upon you,'" Li said.
</P>
<P>
"Now I would like to say the same thing to you," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that middle-aged and older scientists are still China's
leading force in scientific research work, but because young
people are naturally adventurous and imaginative, it is mainly up
to young scientists to accelerate the progress of science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Li talked to the scientists in the Zhongnanhai compound, the
seat of the State Council. Vice-premier Li Lanqing, State
Councillor Song Jian were also present at the meeting. 
