<HEADLINE> Philippine House to Hold Special Sessions on Tax Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine House of
Representatives will hold special sessions beginning April 10 for
the passage of an income tax reform bill, House Speaker Jose de
Venecia said today.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia said the house, originally scheduled to resume on
April 21, will work on the passage of the third phase of the
Comprehensive Tax Reform Package (CTRP), particularly the increase
in individual income tax exemptions.
</P>
<P>
The house failed to approve the legislation on income tax
reform, the last part of the CTRP to be passed by the Congress,
this month due to heated debates and the lack of quorum.
</P>
<P>
The Congress is now on its Lenten recess which started March
21.
</P>
<P>
The congressional passage of the entire CTRP has been set by
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) as one of the conditions for
the Philippines to exit from its supervision.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is expected to get free from the IMF's nearly
35-year-long supervision on its economic development this June.
</P>
