<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Localities Ordered to Reduce Farmers' Burden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee and the State Council have issued a
13-point joint decision ordering all localities and departments to
reduce burdens on farmers by canceling all kinds of illegal levies.
</P>
<P>
While the economic situation in the rural areas is enjoying
overall development, the document says, in some places farmers are
still weighed down by rampant unlawful charges by local
departments.
</P>
<P>
This is a serious infringement upon the legal rights of farmers
and has aroused strong resentment among the rural people, it says.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and the State Council regards the
issue of reducing farmers' burdens as an urgent political task as
well as a long-term policy, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
The decision says that the state will not change its policy on
agricultural taxation, and therefore, during the Ninth Five-Year
Plan period (1996-2000), no new taxes will be charged on farmers
and the rates of existing taxes will not be raised. No localities
have the right to levy new taxes or raise tax rates, the decision
warns.
</P>
<P>
Economic policies regarding charges by villages and local
governments will remain unchanged, it adds.
</P>
<P>
The decision prohibits any means to be used to collect cash and
goods from farmers, who have the right to turn down illegal
charges and to take their cases to the court.
</P>
<P>
Taxation on poor farmers should be reduced, as burdens imposed
on township enterprises, according to the document. Also
prohibited is undue fund-raising in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Town and township governments should cut their staff and
spending, and leading officials at all levels should personally
deal with the issue, the decision says, noting that leading
officials of relevant localities and departments will be hold
responsible where burdens on farmers are found to be increasing.
</P>
<P>
The document requests that the supervisory role of the public
and the media in this regard be strengthened, so as to severely
punish any kind of activities that would increase farmers' burdens.
</P>
<P>
Farmers' properties and legal income must be protected and
their will and democratic rights respected, the document says.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
