<HEADLINE> Yemen's oil revenues Increased Markedly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, March 3l (Xinhua) -- A Yemeni official announced that
revenues of Yemen's oil exports are estimated at 970 million
U.S. dollars at present, showing a marked increase over that of
1995.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Oil and Mineral Wealth Mohammed Said el Attar said
that the export of oil stood at about 650 million dollars in 1995
when then civil war just ended.
</P>
<P>
Attar pointed out that the factors which have caused the
increase of revenues are the rise in the world oil prices, the
drop in the cost of oil products in Yemen and the Yemeni
government's supervision over the oil-producing companies.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni oil minister added that Yemen now produces 380,000
barrels of oil per day, and the output is expected to rise to
420,000 barrels per day by the end of this year. 
</P>
