<HEADLINE> Philippines, Switzerland Ink Investment Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines and Switzerland
today signed an agreement on the promotion and reciprocal
protection of investments that aims to strengthen the two
countries' economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed after a meeting between Philippine
President Fidel Ramos and visiting Head of the Public Economic
Department of the Swiss Federal Council Jean-Pascal Delamuraz.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Ramos expressed confident that the
agreement will result in increased investments from Switzerland,
particularly in the infrastructure, manufacturing, trading and
light industry sectors.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two governments conferred upon each
other a most-favored nation status to maintain favorable
conditions for investments.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also guarantees the free transfer of investment
funds between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Delamuraz arrived here today on a four-day visit to the
Philippines.  
