<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Expected to Open Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market is
expected to open sharply weaker tomorrow, following Wall Street's
huge sell-off before the Easter break.
</P>
<P>
Australian market players have had four days to ponder the
implications of Wall Street's 140.11 point fall to 6740.59 on
Thursday, which came after the local market had closed on a strong
note ahead of the break.
</P>
<P>
Reports over Easter have indicated that further tightening of
US interest rates is on the cards, pointing to bearish days ahead
for equity markets not only on Wall Street but domestically as
well.
</P>
<P>
The US Federal Reserve pushed short term interest rates a
quarter percentage point higher last week as inflationary
pressures emerge in the US economy.
</P>
<P>
The Fed's move was not a one-off event, it would likely move
again to tighten interest rates by another quarter percentage
point to 5.75 percent, possibly timed after the May 20 open
markets committee meeting, said John Peters, senior economist of
Westpac Bank in his weekly economic report published here today.
</P>
</TEXT>
