<HEADLINE> HK Launches Electronic Service for Trade Declarations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Customs and Excise
Department of Hong Kong will launch Electronic Data Interchange
(EDI) service for importers and exporters Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the department said here today that with the
availability of the new service, importers and exporters may
choose between lodging declarations using paper forms, diskettes
or using the EDI service.
</P>
<P>
He said that lodging electronic declarations is more convenient
and the service is available 16 hours a day, seven days a week.
</P>
<P>
He said that importers and exporters can save traveling time
and there will be no need to queue.
</P>
<P>
He said that the introduction of the EDI service is a major
step forward in Hong Kong government's efforts to provide an
efficient and user friendly infrastructure and environment for
business in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the department is going to phase
out the Diskette Submission Scheme by December 1997 and Paper
declarations will be phased out in the next three years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
