<HEADLINE> S. Korean President Urges to Stop Economic Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 31 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim
Young-sam today asked government ministers to map out effective
measures to overcome the financial difficulties and keep the
stability of the nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of ministers of economic affairs, he ordered that
necessary steps be taken to relieve financial difficulties of the
medium- and small-sized enterprises related to the two collapsed
conglomerates.
</P>
<P>
Many big banks and more enterprises are facing worsening
financial problems since the exposure of the loan-for-bribes
scandal of Hanbo Group and the collapse of Sammi Group in the
first two months this year.
</P>
<P>
Kim asked the ministers to speed up the opening of financial
market so that enterprises may get funds from overseas smoothly.
</P>
<P>
For household budgets, Kim emphasized stabilization of farm and
dairy products and daily necessities through an improved
distribution structure and lower prices.
</P>
<P>
He also called for utmost efforts to cut private tutoring and
personal service cost, and stressed the importance of new
technological advances and setting up of joint ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
