<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in dull
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by 25.92 points to close at 2073 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 110.02 million units,
valued at 270.67 million Singapore dollars (about 190.61 million
US dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 287 to 47, while 275
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Labroy was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 6.41 million units. It was followed by MBF Land which
had 4.4 million shares traded. Pacific Can was next with 3.67
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Malaya Banking 200 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 60
cents to finish at 16.2 Singapore dollars. The Overseas Chinese
Banking Corporation (OCBC) gained 35 cents to end at 9.45
Singapore dollars, while MAS closed 32 cents higher at 3.92
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) was
the biggest loser as it declined by 70 cents to end at 16.8
Singapore dollars. Malaya Banking and the Thai Prime Fund fell by
60 cents each to finish at 16.2 Singapore dollars and 10.2 US
dollars respectively. The Sembawang Corporation ended 45 cents
lower at 6.95 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
