<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Ends Official Visit in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of China, ended
a six-day official visit in France and left Paris this morning.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi will make a stopover in Goteborg, Sweden, before going
to Norway for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in France, Qiao met with President Jacques
Chirac, Prime Minister Alain Juppe, French Senate President Rene
Monory and French National Assembly President Philippe Seguin.
</P>
<P>
Qiao discussed with the French leaders the strengthening of
Sino-French relations, and the development of political, economic,
cultural, scientific and technological cooperations between the
two nations.
</P>
<P>
In two separate messages sent today to Monory and Seguin, Qiao
thanked them for their cordial and friendly reception, and
expressed his confidence that China and France will establish a
lasting and steady friendship which is oriented toward the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
France is the first stage of his four-nation visit, which also
includes Norway, Italy and Mongolia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
