<HEADLINE> ABC Sees Sustained Growth of Banking Service in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
(ABC), a former state bank mainly for the country's agricultural
sector and farmers, has witnessed a stable growth of its branches
in Shanghai over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
ABC is now one of the four major commercial banks in China. An
ABC official said it is quite challenging for the bank to compete
with other large commercial banks in cities.
</P>
<P>
After years of effort, banking services for urban industrial
projects and international businesses combined have accounted for
two thirds of the bank's total in Shanghai, said Yan Qifen,
director of ABC's Shanghai branch.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, the bank has granted loans totalling 244.71 billion
yuan to industrial projects, he said, adding that ABC has been
actively involved in the construction of most infrastructural
projects and key industrial projects in Shanghai over the past
years.
</P>
<P>
The bank has so far established 31 sub-branches and 331 banking
offices under its local branch in Shanghai, the country's largest
city, Yan said.
</P>
<P>
The bank has also been very successful in the Pudong New Area,
an emerging financial and trade zone separated from downtown
Shanghai by the Huangpu River, he said.
</P>
<P>
It set up a branch in Pudong in August of 1990, and has so far
issued a total of 60 billion yuan in loans to local projects in
the past six years.
</P>
<P>
"Statistics show that ABC has been playing a leading role in
the Pudong New Area over its counterparts in banking businesses,"
Yan said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bank will take measures to maintain its growth
of businesses in Shanghai this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
