<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build Diamond Trading Center in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China is going to build its
first diamond trading center in the Pudong District in Shanghai,
the country's largest city.
</P>
<P>
The construction work will be undertaken jointly by the
Lujiazui Finance And Trade Zone Development Company from Shanghai
and United Development Incorporated from Israel.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have recently signed an agreement to invest 66
million US dollars for the trading center which will cover a total
area of 35,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that the establishment of the Shanghai diamond
trading center will promote China's diamond exchanges and diamond
jewelry manufacturing trade.
</P>
<P>
The world's diamond trading volume stands around 60 billion US
dollars every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
