<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, Vietnam Conclude Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, march 31 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Vietnam have
concluded cooperation agreements, ranging from fishery to
transport, in a bid to boost their bilateral ties, the Thai news
agency reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The agreements, including those on trade, investment, aviation
and financial cooperation, were concluded during Thai Prime
minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh's visit to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The Thai prime minister arrived in Hanoi on Sunday for a
two-day official visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the pacts concluded, Thailand and Vietnam will increase
weekly flights between Bangkok and Hanoi from five to seven, and
Bangkok to Ho Chi Minh City from seven to nine.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also agreed to increase land transport links
through Laos and Cambodia and conduct new sea demarcation properly
to open the way for fishery cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit and his entourage would return to Bangkok later
Monday, ending the last leg of his tour to the member countries of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The Thai prime minister had earlier visited Indonesia, Brunei,
Malaysia, and Singapore.  
</P>
</TEXT>
