<HEADLINE> Nigerian Military Officers Visit Namibia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen senior Nigerian
military officers have wrapped up a week-long visit to Namibia to
acquaint themselves with the development in the country, said a
source reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commander of Nigeria's National War College (NWC),
Commander Gabriel Siyambade, told Namibian Broadcasting
Corporation's Radio News on Sunday that the visit was to observe
Namibia's achievements since its independence.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian Head of State General Sani Abacha's envoy
Major-General Chris Garuba paid a courtesy call on Namibian
President Sam Nujoma at State House in capital Windhoek where he
delivered a personal message from Abacha.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Namibia, Nigerian officers held talks
with their Namibian counterparts to explore the possibility of
the NWC offering assistance to the Namibian defense force, as
well as strengthen relationships between the two countries.
</P>
