<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Kenyan government on Sunday received support for
sending its troops to repulse a cross-border incursion by
Ethiopian raiders which killed 41 civilians and 16 police
officers in Kenya's northern Marsabit District.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
<P>
-- The festive Easter period came with an added blessing for
the residents of Machakos District and Nairobi city as the
eagerly awaited long rains spread to the parched areas.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- African finance ministers and central bank governors will
brainstorm directly with multilateral lending institutions and
private sector representatives as they tackle the continent's
monumental problems of financial sector reform and debt relief.
</P>
<P>
-- Uganda is projected to register an impressive growth rate
of 7 percent this financial year with agriculture, manufacturing
and construction as the leading sectors, the International
Monetary Fund has said.
</P>
<P>
The East African
</P>
<P>
-- The United States has set up a high-tech monitoring base in
Fort Portal town, western Uganda, to keep track of the war in
Zaire, sources close to the Ugandan Army commander in Kampala
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
