<HEADLINE> 20 Zimbabweans Killed in Easter Holiday Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 Zimbabweans have been
killed, 60 injured in more than 100 accidents reported
countrywide since the beginning of the Easter holidays, police
reports said.
</P>
<P>
This happened despite police deployment which was extended in
an attempt to enforce road traffic regulations during the Easter
holidays.
</P>
<P>
In capital Harare alone, more than 800 tickets worth almost
20,000 U.S. Dollars had been issued during the major blitz.
Police impounded 30 vehicles and arrested 15 motorists for
drunken driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
