<HEADLINE> Foreign-Funded Enterprises in Henan Province add Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded enterprises in
central China's Henan Province exported 359 million US dollars
worth of goods last year, 17.55 percent more than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Major export goods from such enterprises included raw materials
for production of textiles, leather and fur products, machinery
and parts, shoes and headgear, chemicals, and ceramics. Most of
the products were made in the provincial capital of Zhengzhou, the
ancient city of Luoyang, Zhoukou, Xuchang, and Nanyang.
</P>
<P>
The province actually used more than 1.2 billion US dollars of
overseas funds in 1996, up 17.2 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
Henan handled imports and exports totaling 2.57 billion US
dollars in 1996, up 6.8 percent from the previous year, with
exports amounting to nearly 1.9 billion US dollars, a 3.7 percent
increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
