<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Controls Duplicated Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The government of Hebei
province, in north China, has worked out concrete measures to
restrict duplicated production.
</P>
<P>
The province is to control the construction of similar projects
and check up on items which involve an investment of five million
yuan each, said Gong Huanwen, director of the Hebei Provincial
Planning Committee.
</P>
<P>
Projects being built as a result of a wrong policy or those
which are duplicated and expected to incur losses upon operation
will be stopped at once.
</P>
<P>
A provincial survey conducted in 1995 showed that 98 percent of
the 1,083 paper mills in Hebei are small in production scale, and
many manufactured similar products. Its textile mills have 3.7
million spindles, far exceeding the demand.
</P>
<P>
Production of some trades in some areas is out of control, Gong
said, adding that enterprises which consume more energy, use
unsophisticated equipment and produce heavy pollution have been
developing at a rapid rate in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
