<HEADLINE> Five Wounded in Plane Crash in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Five persons, two of them
Philippine Air Force pilots, were injured today following the
explosion and crash of a government fighter plane over Davao city
in southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The two pilots took off at the Davao International Airport at
9:39 a.m. for an observation flight over the Davao Gulf. However,
after 11 minutes, a mid-air explosion was heard by the residents
of Toril district some 21 kilometers west of the city proper.
</P>
<P>
While the two pilots were able to eject from the ill-fated
plane prior to the explosion, the bulk of the burning aircraft hit
a house in the said district, injuring a mother and her two
children inside.
</P>
<P>
All the wounded were brought to the Davao Medical Center for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
An Air Transportation Office official said the pilots were
flying a newly commissioned OB-10 aircraft. The Davao-based
Composite Air Support Force is looking for the wreckage and having
an investigation of the air accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
