<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has The Largest Crane Varieties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINHUANGDAO, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China has a greater variety
of cranes than any other country, according to reports from a
seminar held here on wetland animal protection.
</P>
<P>
Among the 15 varieties of crane in the world, nine live in
China. And the country also has the largest population of rare
cranes which are under the highest level of state protection.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has now some 800 red-crested cranes,
42 percent of the total in the world. It also has 96 percent of
world's 3,000 white cranes, 75 percent of 5,300 white-naped
cranes, and 91 percent of 6,000 black-necked cranes.
</P>
<P>
The crane, as a rare waterbird that inhabits damp areas, is of
great ecological and cultural importance.
</P>
<P>
China has closely watched over the protection of cranes and
other wetland animals in the past several years. Since the 1970s,
the country has set up 45 reserves for protecting cranes and other
wetland animals, covering a total area of 7.8 million hectares.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
