<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Export-Oriented Township Enterprises Grow in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Export-oriented economy has become
a driving force for the development of township enterprises in
east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
For the past six years, the export volume of the enterprises
has been increasing at an annual rate of 51.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Fujian is the hometown of a large number of overseas Chinese,
and has shown its readiness to establish closer ties with overseas
firms. To date, Fujian has approved some 4,390 overseas-funded
township enterprises; 2,500 are now in operation.
</P>
<P>
Hoping to attract overseas investment, the provincial
government has in recent years also channeled substantial funding
toward the construction of some 1,100 industrial zones for rural
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capital has become a major funding source of these
companies, according to the local government, noting that the
contractual overseas capital flowing into the rural enterprises
has totalled six billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, the township enterprises in the province have set up
ten bases to manufacture goods mainly for export. Their total
output value amounted to 287.67 billion yuan last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
