<HEADLINE> Central China Province Controls Population </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENZHOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has now replaced southwestern Sichuan Province as the most
populous province-level areas in the country with 91.72 million
residents.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan can no longer claim in its head count of the people who
live in Chongqing, which has been designated a municipality
directly under the central government.
</P>
<P>
In order to keep in step with local economic development, Henan
will continue its population control efforts by pursing the "one
child per couple" policy.
</P>
<P>
The natural population growth rate in Henan last year reached
7.84 per thousand -- an addition of about 700,000 people.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the number of couples in which the wife is
aged 23 or above, and the husband is 25 or older, has accounted
for nearly 51 percent of the local total, a substantial increase
from the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
And 88.15 percent of babies born last year were within the
set quota for births, up 23.5 percent from 1991.
</P>
<P>
Promotion of the family-planning policy and the extensive use
of birth control information have helped the province check the
momentum of the local population growth.
</P>
<P>
A growing number of women of child-bearing age in the province
are taking contraceptives to control the number of births. The
practice of marrying and giving birth at an older age has been now
accepted by more local people. enditem

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
