<HEADLINE> China to Boost Technology Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official of the
State Science and Technology Commission (SSTC) said that
scientific research institutions are intensifying cooperation with
foreign trade companies to bring a quicker boost to China's
technology export.
</P>
<P>
Dong Jingsheng, director of the Scientific and Technological
Achievements Department of SSTC said at the recent '97 China
Tianjin Foreign Trade Fair that technology export has brought
incentives to China's foreign trade in recent years.
</P>
<P>
China's technology export witnessed an 80 percent growth last
year, standing at 4.7 billion US dollars, he said, noting that the
country's overall foreign trade increased by 1.5 percent at the
same time.
</P>
<P>
Rapid growth was also seen in the sector of hi-tech export, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientific research institutions have actively
participated in foreign trade fairs every year, and received 26
million dollars-worth of orders at the Tianjin Foreign Trade Fair
last year. 
</P>
