<HEADLINE> County of Rich Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, March 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 40 very rich farmers have
made their fortune worth millions of yuan in recent years through
farming in a small county in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
In Jingshan county, one farmer gained property of more than 10
million yuan by investing in agricultural production, and another
40 farmers each have one million yuan-worth of property.
</P>
<P>
Most rich farmers are engaged in animal breeding and fruit tree
planting, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
Placing more importance on agriculture, Jingshan county worked
out a series of preferential policies to woo investment in
agriculture in recent years, thus helping its farmers on the road
to prosperity.
</P>
<P>
As one of 50 trial counties for biological agriculture
development, the county began to reclaim barren mountain land
since 1985. So far, 66,000 ha of cash tree and fruit tree forests
have been built.
</P>
<P>
The county still has abundant resources in mountain areas to be
developed, said the official, noting that there are still of
100,000 ha of barren mountain to be worked.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the per capita income for farmers in the county
exceeded 2,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
