<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Unprecedented Trade Surplus Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's number one trading
partner South Africa enjoyed an unprecedented trade surplus of
about 700 million U.S. Dollars over the first 10 months of last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics from the South African High
Commission in Zimbabwe, Zimbabwe imported goods worth about 900
million US Dollars from South Africa, while its exports were
valued at 200 million Dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
Major exports to South Africa were prepared foodstuffs,
beverages, tobacco, wood and wood products, textiles and textile
products.
</P>
<P>
Imports were made up of machinery, mechanical appliances,
electrical equipment, base metals, chemicals and allied products,
vehicles, transport equipment, aircraft and mineral products.
</P>
