<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Foreign Trade Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
province, a leader in the country's opening process, maintained a
rapid growth rate of nearly 11 percent in foreign trade in the
past two months.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the total foreign trade volume in
the province during the period reached 15.26 billion US dollars,
accounting for 38.9 percent of the country's total. Of this
amount, the export volume reached 8.99 billion US dollars, up 20
percent.
</P>
<P>
State-owned firms are still the mainstay of export, completing
49.4 percent of the total exports in the province.
</P>
<P>
Light and textile products are the major export items. Clothes,
shoes and toys are the first three items on the list of exports.
</P>
<P>
Some 40 percent of the commodities produced in the province
were exported to Hong Kong, while 20 percent went to the United
States, the statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's import volume increased by 0.1 percent to 6.27
billion US dollars in the January-February period. Major import
commodities made up for the short supply in raw materials and
goods, such as plastics, iron and integrated circuits.
</P>
<P>
Japan is the largest supplier of the province's imported
commodities, followed by Taiwan and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
