<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nearly 100 Rape Cases Reported in Zimbabwe Last </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Almost 100 rape cases were
reported throughout Zimbabwe last week, The Herald daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Seventy people were arrested in connection with these
dehumanizing offenses, police statistics for the period show.
</P>
<P>
Officer-in-charge police press and public relation inspector
Mario Dube said the increase in reported cases should not be
regarded as an upsurge in the crime but as an ''increase in the
detection rate''.
</P>
<P>
Dube said, ''this has been due to awareness campaigns on the
need to report such cases. A lot of rape cases in the past went
unreported. In this way, the perpetrators escaped unpunished.''
</P>
<P>
He urged members of the public to report all rape cases to the
police to punish the perpetrators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
