<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Railway Group To Open Twelve High-Speed Passenger Trains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Railway Group
will begin operation of 12 high-speed passenger trains and 11
trains for transporting goods beginning on April 1.
</P>
<P>
Railways controlled by the Guangzhou Railway Group based in
this capital of Guangdong Province are spread throughout the
provinces of Guangdong, Hunan and Hainan.
</P>
<P>
As of April 1, the group will handle 138 pairs of passenger
trains, an increase over the present 127 pairs. The group also
will run 5,140 freight trains daily, a jump over the current 4,770.
</P>
<P>
The speed of the new passenger trains, which boast evening
departure/morning arrival services, will be 8.3 kilometers per
hour faster than at present. These trains will have a traveling
distance of no more than 1,500 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Hours of service for departure will be from 4 to 11 p.m., with
arrival times scheduled from 5 to 11 a.m. the following day.
</P>
<P>
Big cities of Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Chengdu and
Shenyang will be the primary travel terminals.
</P>
<P>
For the newly-operating freight trains, the Guangzhou South
Railway Station, and Dalang and Tangxi stations will be the
departure stations, and Harbin, Shenyang and Changchun, the
terminals. Travel distance of these trains will be from 600 to 800
kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
