<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Takes Measures to Contain Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar government
has banned imports of vegetables and fruits following outbreak of
cholera in the Isles, which has killed three people, and 10
others are admitted to Mnazi Mmoja Hostipal in Zanzibar town.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry's statement on Sunday also banned selling
of ice-cream, juice, eating during festivals including at
weddings and running of open air stalls in the streets.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed that people should boil drinking water
and restrict themselves from eating food sold in the streets as a
precaution against the communicable disease.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, officials with the
Health Ministry said the situation was not serious now. "If the
situation deteriorates we will close restaurants and impose a
quarantine on the affected areas," they said. 
