<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Delegation Begins Latin America Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A top Chinese military
delegation, headed by Vice-Chairman of China's Central Military
Commission General Zhang Wannian, arrived here today for a
four-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
This is the highest ranking Chinese military delegation that
has ever visited Latin America since the People's Republic of
China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the airport, General Zhang said the visit of
the delegation, including Deputy Chief of General Staff General
Qian Shugen and other generals from Chinese air force and navy,
aims to promote mutual understanding, deepen friendship and
further the development between the armies and peoples of China
and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Zhang is scheduled to meet with Argentine
President Carlos Menem, Defense Minister Jorge Dominguez and
senior officers of the Argentine armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Argentina is the first leg of the delegation's Latin America
tour, which will also take them to Chile and Brazil. 
</P>
