<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Students Arrested For Attack On Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Six Sri Lankan students from
three leading schools in Colombo were arrested by police Sunday
night for an attack on staff at the Colombo National Hospital,
according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place when a group of students tried to
forcibly enter the hospital premises to obtain medical attention
for some other students who were injured on Saturday evening in
clashes between rival schools after a cricket match.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the hospital staff tried to prevent the
students from entering the hospital premises as no vehicles are
allowed to enter due to security reasons.
</P>
<P>
The students had then become abusive and later assaulted the
hospital staff and security men, injuring five of them.  
</P>
