<HEADLINE> APEC Plans to Offer Financial Information on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Finance Ministers of the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) are planning to provide
investors with financial information through an Internet home
page, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will discuss the plan to set up the APEC finance
ministry home page at a meeting in Cebu, the Philippines, this
weekend.
</P>
