<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank of China Finances Seed Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
has decided to set aside one billion yuan from its credit funds to
support the "Seed Project," sources here say.
</P>
<P>
China needs 8.7 billion kilograms of various strains annually,
but has a processing capacity of only two billion kilograms,
falling far short of the domestic demand. Therefore top priority
must be given to upgrade technology used in producing seeds.
</P>
<P>
The loans, aimed at boosting the country's agriculture and
grain output, will be used mainly to finance seed improvement
projects approved by the State Council and undertaken by seed
companies in breeding, introducing new strains, processing and
packing, as well as importing new technology to update existing
equipment.
</P>
<P>
China lags far behind developed countries in terms of seed
cultivation, production and processing. Backward seed technology
and poor quality plus small-scale production have long
bottlenecked the country's agriculture development, especially
grain production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
