<HEADLINE> China Releases White Paper on Progress in Human Rights Cause in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- China today released a white
paper on the progress in its human rights cause in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The white paper, entitled "Progress in China's Human Rights
Cause in 1996," and released by the Information Office of the State
Council, is a comprehensive reflection of the progress that China
has scored in its human rights cause in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The 13,000-character white paper includes seven parts: One:
