<HEADLINE> Anhui to Open Trade Center in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province will
open a trade center in New York this May to help local industrial
firms engaged in keen international competition.
</P>
<P>
The center, located in Manhattan, was jointly built by the
Saveswork Construction Development Co. of the United States and
the New Technology Development Co. in Anhui.
</P>
<P>
It will have 40 founding members, which are well-performing
state-owned enterprises of various sizes, and township-run and
individual enterprises chosen from across China.
</P>
<P>
The center is to help its members register themselves in the
United States, organize international exhibitions, expand
wholesales, seal contracts with their clients and receive fresh
market information.  
