<HEADLINE> Garcia Wins Criterium Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Marcelino Garcia of Spain claimed
the two-day Criterium International cycling race in Castres,
France on Sunday, beating ONCE teammate Laurent Jalabert of France
into second place by 50 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Another Spaniard, Aitor Garmendia, won the eight-kilometer
third stage time-trial around Castres, edging out last year's
winner Chris Boardman of Britain by three seconds, to leave Garcia
out in front overall.
</P>
<P>
Pascal Lino of France was third 54 seconds off the pace before
Italy's Marco Pantani, at one minute 10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Garcia, 26 and a professional since 1994, achieved his first
major career win by taking the second road stage on Sunday, an
80km run which ended at the summit of the 1185-meter Pic de Nore
mountain. The Spaniard escaped 10km from the finish to see off
the chasing pack by a clear minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
