<DOCNO> XIE19970331.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-30 21:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Resolution Suggests Suspension of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League Council tonight
called for suspending normalization steps between Arab states and
Israel in a significant move designed to force Israel to back down
from its hardline policies.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from the 22-member league, during their
evening session, approved a resolution proposed by Syria calling
for freezing all steps to normalize ties with Israel in response
to Israel's Judaization attempt on Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution envisages the closures of legations and
bureaus until Israel abides by the Madrid conference principles,
the land-for-peace principle, and all agreements reached during
the peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The resolution also recommended the suspension of Arab
participation in the multilateral peace talks on the achievement
of full-fledged peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League Council meeting, though a routine one, came as
a critical timing as Israel broke ground for the 6,500-unit Jewish
neighborhood in East Jerusalem, a move that has sparked
Palestinian rioting on the 10th day running and put the peace
process in jeopardy.
</P>
<P>
Israel has diplomatic ties with Egypt and Jordan and set up
trade links with Morocco, Tunisia, Qatar and Oman.
</P>
<P>
Arab foreign ministers, at their evening session, also approved
the draft resolutions they examined earlier in the day on
developments of the Arab-Israeli conflict, the Palestinian cause,
Jerusalem, development on Palestinian lands, the Palestinian
Intifada (uprising), settlement activities in occupied lands and
Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will meet tomorrow morning to discuss a number of
draft resolutions on other political issues on their
agenda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
